<h2>
    <a href="/blog/moir%C3%A9-patterns-in-a-pair-of-hexagonal-lattices/">Moiré patterns in a pair of hexagonal lattices</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    in
    
    <a href="/blog/category/featured-on-frontpage/">Featured on frontpage</a>
    
    
    
    on 25 Sep 2018
</h6>





<a href="/blog/moir%C3%A9-patterns-in-a-pair-of-hexagonal-lattices/">
    <img class="img-thumbnail pull-left" src="/static/media/uploads/blog/hex_lattice/.thumbnails/lattice.png/lattice-90x90.png">
</a>





<p>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moir%C3%A9_pattern">Moiré pattern</a> is an interference pattern that occurs when two grids of repeating lines or shapes are rotated by a small amount relative to one another (<a href="https://www.xkcd.com/1814/">oblig. xkcd</a>).</p>




<div class="blog-list-detail">
    
    
    <p>
